Defendant Jose M Gomez in court with attorney Robert J Hampton.  Matthew James Torbenson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, with credit for 87 days time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 18 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Serve 60 days in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review.
-Parenting classes.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No unsupervised contact with victim M.W.G unless approved by the agent and BMCW/CPS.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay the DNA surcharge during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 
-Court WAIVED all other court costs, fees, and surcharges due to inability to pay.
-Provide DNA Sample.
-Restitution set at ZERO.
